2. If the index reaches the end of the list of skins, calculate the values for the trade-up list and store the result.

3. Otherwise, for each wear of the current skin, add the skin to the trade-up list and call the `generateCombinations` method recursively with the updated list and the next index.

4. To calculate the values for a specific trade-up, you can use your existing `TradeUps` class methods, such as the average profitability and cost.

